    <activity>
        <p>
            <term>Work in Groups to:</term>
        </p>
        <p>
            Use a <m>15</m> cm ruler to measure the length of the locker repeated times and record the observation in the table below.
        </p>
        <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
            <row header="yes">
                <cell>Attempt</cell>
                <cell>Measurement (cm)</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
                <cell><m>1</m></cell>
                <cell>?</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
                <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                <cell>?</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
                <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                <cell>?</cell>
            </row>
        </tabular>
        <p>
            Do you get the same results, Explain?
        </p>
        <p>
            Find the difference between the measurement attempts?
        </p>
        <p>
            Mr Zachariah Mbasu used a <m>90</m> cm ruler to measure the length of the locker and found out that the length is exactly the same as your second attempt.
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol marker="(a)">
                <li>
                    <p>
                        What is the exact length of the locker?
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        What is the difference between your second attempt and the exact length of the locker, why?
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        What is the difference between your first attempt and the exact length of the locker?
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                         What is the difference between your third attempt and the exact length of the locker?
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                       What is the quotient of the difference between your first attempt and the exact length of the locker and the exact length of the locker? 
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                         What is the quotient of the difference between your third attempt and the exact length of the locker and the exact length of the locker?
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Find the percentages of these quotients in (e) and (f). Which one is greater and why?
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>


     


